Class Enumerator

java.lang.Object
  xxl.core.pipes.queryGraph.AbstractNode
      xxl.core.pipes.sources.AbstractSource<Integer>

All Implemented Interfaces:
Node, Source<Integer>, MetaDataManageable<Object,Object>, MetaDataProvider<CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>
public class Enumerator
extends AbstractSource<Integer>

Source component in a query graph that delivers an ascending or descending sequence of integer objects.

Example usage (1): 

        new VisualSink(new Enumerator(10, 1000), true);
Returns the integers 0, ..., 9 with a delay of one second between two successive values.

Since:
1.1
See Also:
SourceProcessor

The output rate is not measured. Returns a sequence from 0 to number-1.

Method Detail

next

public Integer next()
             throws NoSuchElementException
Defines the next element to be transferred. The implementation is as follows: 

        if (up ? next < to : next > to)
                return new Integer(up ? next++ : next--);
        throw new NoSuchElementException();
